                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Stuart, J. Leighton; Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-23T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 23, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>515. You will have seen from Deptel 513 Apr 23 which crossed your 841 Apr 23 that
                    it is not Dept’s intention that you should make precipitous departure from China
                    following Commie takeover. On contrary Dept attaches greatest importance your
                    attempting informally to regularize situation of Amer communities in Commie
                    territory and of Amer Cons therein.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
